From 1dd67b116b4b695cc293c00e95c15a6122d6457a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sudhanshu <sambastha@salesforce.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 23:45:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] feat(analytics): add consent notice + Consent Mode v2
 defaults (PR-2 of conversion-tracking)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the disclosure-only cookie notice and the Consent Mode v2 default
block per plan.md §2.8.

- index.html: inline `gtag('consent', 'default', ...)` block before any
  GTM/gtag.js loader. All four flags (`analytics_storage`, `ad_storage`,
  `ad_user_data`, `ad_personalization`) ship as `granted` so the very
  first page-view respects parkspot's disclosure-only posture.
- OrganismConsentNotice.vue: fixed-bottom strip with the locked copy,
  a Privacy Policy link to /privacy, and a single "Got it" button. No
  Reject / Manage Preferences UI. Acknowledgement persists in
  localStorage under `parkspot_consent_notice` with a 12-month TTL;
  reads/writes are wrapped in try/catch so Safari private mode doesn't
  throw. Slides in ~1s after mount.
- App.vue: mounts the notice under \`<ClientOnly>\` for SSG safety
  (matches existing pattern for OrganismLogin/AtomChat).
- Spec pins the disclosure-only contract (single button, TTL re-show,
  localStorage failure tolerance).

Posture is reversible — flipping defaults to \`denied\` and adding
Accept buttons becomes a one-PR change against \`setDefault\` /
\`updateConsent\` in src/lib/analytics/consent.js.
