Replaces the direct gtag.js + AW-586763140 block with the GTM container
(GTM-KDFHGZN) per plan.md §2.9. All conversions are now wired from
inside the GTM container, which makes future tag changes a no-deploy
operation.

- Deleted the <!-- Google tag --> block that loaded
  https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-779VHE86MJ and called
  gtag('config', ...) for both GA4 and Google Ads.
- Moved the Consent Mode default block to the very top of <head> and
  placed the GTM head snippet immediately after it. Order matters:
  consent default MUST execute before GTM loads so the first page-view
  respects parkspot's disclosure-only posture.
- Uncommented the GTM <noscript> iframe at the top of <body> for the
  ~1% of visitors with JS disabled.
- Removed the now-redundant commented-out GTM block at the bottom of
  <body>.

Hard-blocked operationally on the GTM container being published in
production (Phase 4A). Code lands on the branch ahead of merge so the
final cutover is just a deploy.
