From 8df6e710b0a9bf1904e81aff58406e922b985704 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sudhanshu <sambastha@salesforce.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 23:57:01 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] feat(analytics): instrument lead funnels VO/SO/Contact
 (PR-4 of conversion-tracking)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wires Phase 2.3, 2.4 and 2.6 of campaign-conversion-tracking/plan.md
into the existing src/lib/analytics public API (PR-1). No direct
gtag/dataLayer access; every push goes through track().

* Router page_view (src/main.js): router.afterEach hook fires
  EVENTS.PAGE_VIEW with page_path/page_title/page_referrer on every
  SPA route change. GA4 admin must disable "Enhanced Measurement →
  Page changes based on browser history events" to avoid
  double-counting against this hook (admin task, no code action).

* Funnel A — VO lead (vo-portal/ParkingRequestForm.vue,
  PageVOPortal.vue): funnel_view on mount, form_start on first
  non-empty blur (gated), form_error on invalid submit (errors keyed
  by field name, comma-joined), form_submit_attempt before API,
  generate_lead with lead_type=parking_seeker / value=500 /
  enhanced_conversion_data after requestSpot resolves cleanly.

* Funnel B — SO register (so-portal/RegisterRequestForm.vue,
  PageSOPortal.vue): same shape as A plus image_upload_start /
  image_upload_complete around ImageUploadService.uploadImages(),
  generate_lead with lead_type=parking_owner / value=1000 /
  expected_rent (analytics segmentation only — value stays the
  locked rupees-1000 proxy per spec section 1.4).

* Funnel C — Contact (organisms/OrganismContactForm.vue,
  PageContactUs.vue): same shape as A. generate_lead with
  lead_type=contact / value=100 fires from PageContactUs after
  onlyContact resolves.

* Thank-you (PageThankYou.vue): reads ?from=, fires lead_confirmed
  with the matching funnel_name (vo->vo_lead, so->so_register,
  contact->contact). Missing/unknown ?from= logs a dev warning and
  skips the event — lead_confirmed is a sanity check, not a
  conversion.

* Redirect call sites updated to include query: { from: ... }:
  PageVOPortal (vo), PageSOPortal (so), PageContactUs (contact),
  plus the three other contact-form-driven thankYou pushes
  (PageHome x2, PageBlogPost, AutomateParking) so PageThankYou's
  funnel_name resolution works on those paths too.

* Tests updated where existing assertions on { name: 'thankYou' }
  needed the new query: PageVOPortal.spec.js, PageBlogPost.spec.js,
  PageHome.spec.js. No new test files added.

Email/phone are passed plain inside enhanced_conversion_data only on
generate_lead; GTM does the SHA-256 hashing client-side. Phone is
normalized to E.164 (+91 prefix for India) at conversion time. No
PII is logged or persisted outside that block.

All track() calls are SSR-safe via the wrapper's typeof window guard
(no try/catch added at call sites). Components import only from
@/lib/analytics (the public surface) — never from dataLayer.js or
attribution.js directly.
